                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108012">Daventry</placeName> and <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>, The Symond Holding.

<persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> son of <persName>
                              <forename>Robert</forename> 
                              <surname>Gymme</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> grants to <persName nymRef="Symond">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> wife of <persName>
                              <forename>Robert</forename> 
                              <surname>Symond</surname> of D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Symond">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> her daughter</persName> three half-acres of arable land in <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>, viz. in the South field, ½ acre over <placeName type="minor">Mereforlong</placeName> by the land of John of M——, 1 rood over <placeName type="minor">Olnesbrech</placeName> by the land of the said Matilda. In the North field ½ acre over <placeName type="minor">Ryelondesmor</placeName>, ½ acre over <placeName type="minor">Fichelesthorn</placeName>; from Michaelmas 17 E. III. for 8 years. Also 5 roods of arable lying under <placeName type="minor">Cleypitteshul</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Jordan</forename> 
                           <surname>Philip</surname>
                        </persName>.
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Wyllymet</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>aula</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Jordan</forename> 
                           <surname>Scon</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Baudewyne</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>aula</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> 
                        <origDate when="1343">
                           <supplied>Mich. 1343.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
